body_text.text:
All potential renal transplant candidates should receive immunization for hepatitis B, pneumococcus, and other standard immunizations appropriate for age. Up-to-date recommendations for routine adult immunizations are available through the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention website (
www.cdc.gov/nip/rec/adult-schedule.pdf
). Immunizations should ideally be administered at least 4 to 6 weeks before transplantation to achieve optimal immune response and to minimize the possibility of live vaccine–derived infection in the post-transplantation period. Household members, close contacts, and health care workers should also be fully immunized.
